<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>For Anjali 💖</title>
  <style>
    body {
      margin: 0;
      font-family: 'Segoe UI', Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif;
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #ff9a9e, #fad0c4);
      display: flex;
      justify-content: center;
      align-items: center;
      height: 100vh;
    }

    .letter {
      background: white;
      padding: 30px;
      max-width: 600px;
      border-radius: 20px;
      box-shadow: 0 10px 30px rgba(0,0,0,0.2);
      text-align: center;
      animation: fadeIn 1.5s ease-in-out;
    }

    h1 {
      color: #ff4d6d;
    }

    p {
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      line-height: 1.6;
      color: #444;
    }

    .signature {
      margin-top: 20px;
      font-weight: bold;
      color: #ff4d6d;
    }

    @keyframes fadeIn {
      from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(20px); }
      to { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

  <div class="letter">
    <h1>Hey Anjali 💖</h1>

    <p>
      Thank you for being such an amazing part of my life. You make everything feel happier, lighter, and honestly a lot more special.
    </p>

    <p>
      I’m really proud of you and how hard you’re working in class 8. I know you’re going to do great things, and I truly believe you’ll achieve a 4 GPA in class 10. You’re smart, strong, and way more capable than you think.
    </p>

    <p>
      No matter what happens, I’ll always be here cheering for you. Study hard, shine bright, and don’t forget… someone is always thinking about you 😉
    </p>

    <p>
      And yeah… Aayush will always love you ❤️
    </p>

    <div class="signature">
      — Yours, Aayush 💫
    </div>
  </div>

</body>
</html>